name: Blow Out
overview: Blow Out is a miscellaneous shooter for the Commodore 64. It was developed by Bob Root using Garry Kitchen's GameMaker. The year of release is unknown. You control a tank that starts on the bottom of the screen. There are several sections which enemies cross. Your goal is to wipe out as many enemies as you can without losing all your lives. Be careful, because as the game progresses, the enemies speed up. The enemies themselves do not shoot you, instead they kill you by running you down.
